As you can see, the disease

142
00:11:32,775 --> 00:11:34,693
-could be anywhere in his body.
-Dr. Cha.

143
00:11:35,194 --> 00:11:38,823
We got a call earlier from the KCDC
about that friend who came back from India

144
00:11:38,906 --> 00:11:40,991
-whom he met last week.
-How is that person doing?

145
00:11:41,075 --> 00:11:42,993
A slight fever right after
he came back to Korea.

146
00:11:43,077 --> 00:11:45,830
It lasted for about two days,
and he's fine right now.

147
00:11:46,163 --> 00:11:48,124
But they say it could be
a slight infection

148
00:11:48,207 --> 00:11:50,334
or an infection that's asymptomatic.

149
00:11:50,751 --> 00:11:54,088
-We can't rule out Nipah virus.
-Of course.

150
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:58,134
But there are symptoms
that are irrelevant to Nipah virus.

151
00:11:58,217 --> 00:12:01,095
We can't take a CT or an MRI here.

152
00:12:01,178 --> 00:12:03,013
-How can we diagnose him?
-Try what we can.

153
00:12:03,097 --> 00:12:05,558
Doctors need to become
the examination equipment.

154
00:12:05,641 --> 00:12:07,810
We need to become
the examination equipment?

155
00:12:11,856 --> 00:12:12,940
Can you all hear me?

156
00:12:13,649 --> 00:12:14,692
-Yes.
-Yes.

157
00:12:17,027 --> 00:12:18,237
A 68-year-old man.

158
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:20,197
He came to the hospital
because of headaches,

159
00:12:20,281 --> 00:12:22,658
a loss of appetite,
and fatigue for about a year.

160
00:12:22,741 --> 00:12:24,952
Recently started vomiting, headaches,
and chest pains.

161
00:12:25,035 --> 00:12:28,038
And now, he's showing new symptoms
such as increased heart rate,

162
00:12:28,122 --> 00:12:29,832
disorientation, seizures, and palpitation.

163
00:12:29,915 --> 00:12:33,252
Dr. Cha thinks the patient
might not have the Nipah virus.

164
00:12:33,335 --> 00:12:36,422
I want each of you to be in charge
of each system and find a disease

165
00:12:36,505 --> 00:12:38,299
that could turn into systemic disease.

166
00:12:38,924 --> 00:12:41,302
-Won-hee, you're in charge of the lungs.
-Okay.

167
00:12:42,428 --> 00:12:45,264
-Si-young, you're in charge of the heart.
-Okay.

168
00:12:45,347 --> 00:12:48,100
-Mi-rae, metabolic system.
-Okay.

169
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:49,602
Jun, the brain.

170
00:12:50,978 --> 00:12:51,812
Okay.

171
00:12:51,896 --> 00:12:53,564
Dr. Lee, digestive system.

172
00:12:53,981 --> 00:12:55,941
-Okay.
-I'll make the overall diagnosis.

173
00:12:56,025 --> 00:12:56,859
Begin.

174
00:12:57,234 --> 00:12:58,152
-Okay.
-Okay.

175
00:13:05,201 --> 00:13:08,621
Dr. Cha, could it be
a chronic lung disease?

176
00:13:08,954 --> 00:13:12,166
It's associated with chest pains,
fatigue, and palpitation.

177
00:13:13,626 --> 00:13:15,794
-What about his heart?
-Blood pressure normal, not obese,

178
00:13:15,878 --> 00:13:17,004
non-smoker, not diabetic.

179
00:13:17,087 --> 00:13:19,173
Nothing in particular
that could affect his heart.

180
00:13:19,715 --> 00:13:22,343
Never had myocardial infarction,
angina, or cardiac insufficiency.

181
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:24,094
How's his X-ray?

182
00:13:27,306 --> 00:13:29,266
I can see a hint
of pneumonic infiltration.

183
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:31,685
Pneumonic infiltration? Next.

184
00:13:31,769 --> 00:13:33,229
The arteriovenous malformation

185
00:13:33,312 --> 00:13:36,106
that occurred in his brain and spinal cord
could affect his entire body.

186
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:39,443
It also explains his headaches, seizure,
and dysaesthesia.

187
00:13:40,069 --> 00:13:41,862
Is the patient's name Yu Deok-kyu?

188
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:43,781
Yes. Why do you ask?

189
00:13:44,532 --> 00:13:46,033
Does he have white hair?

190
00:13:48,994 --> 00:13:50,996
Are you in the security office?
How'd you know that?

191
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:52,831
-You didn't even see him.
-Do you know him?

192
00:13:55,626 --> 00:13:58,212
Yes. I think so.

193
00:13:58,712 --> 00:14:00,339
It's the best thing I heard so far.

194
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:02,550
-Do you know him well?
-I met only him a few times

195
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:04,885
during my volunteer medical service,
I don't know him well.

196
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:07,596
-But I do know his job.
-What is it?

197
00:14:09,306 --> 00:14:10,474
He's a priest.

198
00:14:15,521 --> 00:14:17,773
-He's wearing a rosary ring.
-A priest?

199
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:19,608
What was he like?

200
00:14:19,984 --> 00:14:22,111
Tell me what kind of priest
or person he was.

201
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:26,740
He was an honest man
both in and outside of the church.

202
00:14:26,824 --> 00:14:29,702
He did a lot of volunteer work
and good deeds.

203
00:14:30,786 --> 00:14:32,121
Really gets me thinking sometimes.

204
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:34,707
I'm an atheist,
but I really do wonder sometimes.

205
00:14:35,207 --> 00:14:36,458
If there really is a deity,

206
00:14:36,959 --> 00:14:39,837
why does such a religious
and kind person have to suffer?

207
00:14:42,131 --> 00:14:43,007
That's religion.

208
00:14:44,091 --> 00:14:45,718
Does religion make people suffer?

209
00:14:47,344 --> 00:14:49,263
How is his build now? Is he thin?

210
00:14:49,597 --> 00:14:50,973
Yes. Why?

211
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:53,601
BODY WEIGHT: 67KG

212
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:54,977
One more symptom.

213
00:14:55,853 --> 00:14:56,979
Rapid weight loss.

214
00:14:57,897 --> 00:15:01,734
He's lost at least 20kg
since half a year ago.

215
00:15:01,817 --> 00:15:03,986
At that time, he was pretty well-built.

216
00:15:04,069 --> 00:15:06,655
Any disease that might have caused
the weight loss?

217
00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:09,950
No. He doesn't have diabetes
or thyroid diseases.

218
00:15:10,701 --> 00:15:13,037
We don't know about cancer
or infection yet, though.

219
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:17,708
Before, he didn't even have
any common geriatric diseases.

220
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:20,461
Why did he suddenly start getting
all these symptoms a year ago?

221
00:15:33,766 --> 00:15:34,934
Are you okay?

222
00:15:36,185 --> 00:15:37,478
What's wrong?

223
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:39,939
My arm hurts so much.

224
00:15:41,273 --> 00:15:44,193
Dr. Cha, Ms. Lee Da-hae
has pain in her arm.

225
00:15:44,693 --> 00:15:48,572
-Please calm her down.
-Ms. Lee, are you okay?

226
00:15:50,282 --> 00:15:51,158
Dr. Heo.

227
00:15:52,701 --> 00:15:53,953
Jun.

228
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:04,922
Pull yourself together, Dr. Heo.

229
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:07,883
Jun.

230
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:12,012
Yes, Dr. Cha. I'm here.

231
00:16:12,554 --> 00:16:13,722
Solve it.

232
00:16:15,057 --> 00:16:16,517
You promised me you'd solve it.

233
00:16:17,518 --> 00:16:20,354
The longer you wait, the harder
it'll get for both you and her.

234
00:16:27,361 --> 00:16:28,737
-Dr. Cha.
-I'm listening.

235
00:16:30,864 --> 00:16:32,616
I'll reduce her pain first.

236
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:34,994
She's suffering too much.

237
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:37,162
Inject an analgesic.

238
00:16:37,621 --> 00:16:39,873
Ms. Lee, you'll be injected
with an analgesic.

239
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:02,229
What's the reason?

240
00:17:03,397 --> 00:17:05,107
What made you want to tell the truth?

241
00:17:08,235 --> 00:17:11,113
If it's phantom limb pain,
it might not be your fault.

242
00:17:11,196 --> 00:17:13,741
PHANTOM LIMB PAIN: PAIN IN A LIMB
THAT HAS BEEN CUT OFF

243
00:17:13,824 --> 00:17:16,035
Her pain might not be my fault.

244
00:17:17,578 --> 00:17:19,288
But if I keep hiding the truth,

245
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:23,834
it might make it harder to diagnose her.

246
00:17:26,795 --> 00:17:27,963
Get ready.

247
00:17:28,630 --> 00:17:31,675
-Can I go inside?
-I like your answer.

248
00:17:34,136 --> 00:17:37,973
It wasn't to feel less guilty
or because you felt sorry for the patient.

249
00:17:38,265 --> 00:17:40,017
You just wanted an accurate diagnosis.

250
00:17:54,448 --> 00:17:55,449
Sir.

251
00:17:57,242 --> 00:17:58,702
Mr. Yu, are you awake?

252
00:18:00,996 --> 00:18:01,997
Mr. Yu.

253
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:05,542
I'm anesthesiologist Cha Yo-han.

254
